target: audio
validations:
  - name: web_audio_initialization
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the audio system initializes a Web Audio API AudioContext with a
        gain node hierarchy: masterGain -> musicGain and sfxGain. Initialization
        must be wrapped in a try/catch so that if the AudioContext constructor fails,
        the game continues without audio. All audio functions must check if audioCtx
        is null before proceeding.

  - name: sound_effects_catalog
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the playSound function supports at minimum these named effects:
        purchase, build, breed_success, animal_death, research_complete, notification,
        click, error. Each effect must be defined with parameters (frequency, duration,
        waveform) and produce audible output when called. Unknown sound names must be
        silently ignored (no crash).

  - name: volume_control
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify a setVolume function accepts a category ('music', 'sfx', or 'master')
        and a level (0.0 to 1.0). It must update the corresponding gain node's value.
        The level must be clamped to [0, 1]. Volume settings must be stored in
        state.audio.musicVolume and state.audio.sfxVolume and persist across save/load.

  - name: background_music
    type: agent_validation
    severity: warning
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify background music can be started and stopped. The music must loop
        continuously (either via an external looping audio file or procedural
        generation). Starting music when it is already playing must be a no-op.
        Stopping music must cleanly disconnect all audio nodes.

  - name: graceful_degradation
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: >
        Verify the game functions correctly when audio is unavailable. If audioCtx
        is null (initialization failed), all calls to playSound, startMusic, stopMusic,
        and setVolume must be no-ops that do not throw errors. The game loop, UI, and
        all other subsystems must work normally without audio.
